SYNOPSIS Adds a new section to a Client-Side page
SYNTAX Add-PnPClientSidePageSection [-Page] &lt;ClientSidePagePipeBind&gt; -SectionTemplate &lt;CanvasSectionTemplate&gt; [-Order &lt;Int32&gt;] [-ZoneEmphasis &lt;Int32&gt;] [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPClientSidePageSection -Page &#34;MyPage&#34; -SectionTemplate OneColumn Adds a new one-column section to the Client-Side page &lsquo;MyPage&rsquo;
EXAMPLE 2 Add-PnPClientSidePageSection -Page &#34;MyPage&#34; -SectionTemplate ThreeColumn -Order 10 Adds a new Three columns section to the Client-Side page &lsquo;MyPage&rsquo; with an order index of 10
EXAMPLE 3 $page = Add-PnPClientSidePage -Name &#34;MyPage&#34; PS&gt; Add-PnPClientSidePageSection -Page $page -SectionTemplate OneColumn Adds a new one column section to the Client-Side page &lsquo;MyPage&rsquo;

SYNOPSIS Adds a text element to a client-side page.
SYNTAX Default Add-PnPClientSideText [-Page] &lt;ClientSidePagePipeBind&gt; -Text &lt;String&gt; [-Order &lt;Int32&gt;] [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] Positioned Add-PnPClientSideText [-Page] &lt;ClientSidePagePipeBind&gt; -Text &lt;String&gt; [-Order &lt;Int32&gt;] -Section &lt;Int32&gt; -Column &lt;Int32&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION Adds a new text element to a section on a client-side page.
EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPClientSideText -Page &#34;MyPage&#34; -Text &#34;Hello World!&#34; Adds the text &lsquo;Hello World!&rsquo; to the Client-Side Page &lsquo;MyPage&rsquo;

SYNOPSIS Adds a content type to a document set
SYNTAX Add-PnPContentTypeToDocumentSet -ContentType &lt;ContentTypePipeBind[]&gt; -DocumentSet &lt;DocumentSetPipeBind&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPContentTypeToDocumentSet -ContentType &#34;Test CT&#34; -DocumentSet &#34;Test Document Set&#34; This will add the content type called &lsquo;Test CT&rsquo; to the document set called &lsquo;&lsquo;Test Document Set&rsquo;
EXAMPLE 2 $docset = Get-PnPDocumentSetTemplate -Identity &#34;Test Document Set&#34; $ct = Get-PnPContentType -Identity &#34;Test CT&#34; Add-PnPContentTypeToDocumentSet -ContentType $ct -DocumentSet $docset This will add the content type called &lsquo;Test CT&rsquo; to the document set called &lsquo;&lsquo;Test Document Set&rsquo;

SYNOPSIS Creates a new document set in a library.
SYNTAX Add-PnPDocumentSet -List &lt;ListPipeBind&gt; -Name &lt;String&gt; -ContentType &lt;ContentTypePipeBind&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPDocumentSet -List &#34;Documents&#34; -ContentType &#34;Test Document Set&#34; -Name &#34;Test&#34; This will add a new document set based upon the &lsquo;Test Document Set&rsquo; content type to a list called &lsquo;Documents&rsquo;. The document set will be named &lsquo;Test&rsquo;
PARAMETERS -Connection Optional connection to be used by the cmdlet.

SYNOPSIS Adds an existing site column to a content type
SYNTAX Add-PnPFieldToContentType -Field &lt;FieldPipeBind&gt; -ContentType &lt;ContentTypePipeBind&gt; [-Required] [-Hidden] [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPFieldToContentType -Field &#34;Project_Name&#34; -ContentType &#34;Project Document&#34; This will add an existing site column with an internal name of &ldquo;Project_Name&rdquo; to a content type called &ldquo;Project Document&rdquo;
PARAMETERS -Connection Optional connection to be used by the cmdlet. Retrieve the value for this parameter by either specifying -ReturnConnection on Connect-PnPOnline or by executing Get-PnPConnection.

SYNOPSIS Adds a publishing page
SYNTAX Add-PnPPublishingPage -PageName &lt;String&gt; [-FolderPath &lt;String&gt;] -PageTemplateName &lt;String&gt; [-Title &lt;String&gt;] [-Publish] [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPPublishingPage -PageName &#39;OurNewPage&#39; -Title &#39;Our new page&#39; -PageTemplateName &#39;ArticleLeft&#39; Creates a new page based on the pagelayout &lsquo;ArticleLeft&rsquo;
EXAMPLE 2 Add-PnPPublishingPage -PageName &#39;OurNewPage&#39; -Title &#39;Our new page&#39; -PageTemplateName &#39;ArticleLeft&#39; -Folder &#39;/Pages/folder&#39; Creates a new page based on the pagelayout &lsquo;ArticleLeft&rsquo; with a site relative folder path

SYNOPSIS Adds a user to a SharePoint group
SYNTAX Internal Add-PnPUserToGroup -LoginName &lt;String&gt; -Identity &lt;GroupPipeBind&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] External Add-PnPUserToGroup -Identity &lt;GroupPipeBind&gt; -EmailAddress &lt;String&gt; [-SendEmail] [-EmailBody &lt;String&gt;] [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPUserToGroup -LoginName user@company.com -Identity &#39;Marketing Site Members&#39; Add the specified user to the SharePoint group &ldquo;Marketing Site Members&rdquo;
EXAMPLE 2 Add-PnPUserToGroup -LoginName user@company.com -Identity 5 Add the specified user to the SharePoint group with Id 5

SYNOPSIS Adds a wiki page
SYNTAX WithContent Add-PnPWikiPage -ServerRelativePageUrl &lt;String&gt; -Content &lt;String&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] WithLayout Add-PnPWikiPage -ServerRelativePageUrl &lt;String&gt; -Layout &lt;WikiPageLayout&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Add-PnPWikiPage -PageUrl &#39;/sites/demo1/pages/wikipage.aspx&#39; -Content &#39;New WikiPage&#39; Creates a new wiki page &lsquo;/sites/demo1/pages/wikipage.aspx&rsquo; and sets the content to &lsquo;New WikiPage&rsquo;
PARAMETERS -Connection Optional connection to be used by the cmdlet. Retrieve the value for this parameter by either specifying -ReturnConnection on Connect-PnPOnline or by executing Get-PnPConnection.

