SYNOPSIS Retrieves a document set template
SYNTAX Get-PnPDocumentSetTemplate [-Identity] &lt;DocumentSetPipeBind&gt; [-Web &lt;WebPipeBind&gt;] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [-Includes &lt;String[]&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Get-PnPDocumentSetTemplate -Identity &#34;Test Document Set&#34; This will get the document set template with the name &ldquo;Test Document Set&rdquo;
EXAMPLE 2 Get-PnPDocumentSetTemplate -Identity &#34;0x0120D520005DB65D094035A241BAC9AF083F825F3B&#34; This will get the document set template with the id &ldquo;0x0120D520005DB65D094035A241BAC9AF083F825F3B&rdquo;
PARAMETERS -Connection Optional connection to be used by the cmdlet. Retrieve the value for this parameter by either specifying -ReturnConnection on Connect-PnPOnline or by executing Get-PnPConnection.

SYNOPSIS Imports a taxonomy from either a string array or a file
SYNTAX Direct Import-PnPTaxonomy [-Terms &lt;String[]&gt;] [-Lcid &lt;Int32&gt;] [-TermStoreName &lt;String&gt;] [-Delimiter &lt;String&gt;] [-SynchronizeDeletions] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] File Import-PnPTaxonomy -Path &lt;String&gt; [-Lcid &lt;Int32&gt;] [-TermStoreName &lt;String&gt;] [-Delimiter &lt;String&gt;] [-SynchronizeDeletions] [-Connection &lt;PnPConnection&gt;] [&lt;CommonParameters&gt;] DESCRIPTION EXAMPLES EXAMPLE 1 Import-PnPTaxonomy -Terms &#39;Company|Locations|Stockholm&#39; Creates a new termgroup, &lsquo;Company&rsquo;, a termset &lsquo;Locations&rsquo; and a term &lsquo;Stockholm&rsquo;
EXAMPLE 2 Import-PnPTaxonomy -Terms &#39;Company|Locations|Stockholm|Central&#39;,&#39;Company|Locations|Stockholm|North&#39; Creates a new termgroup, &lsquo;Company&rsquo;, a termset &lsquo;Locations&rsquo;, a term &lsquo;Stockholm&rsquo; and two subterms: &lsquo;Central&rsquo;, and &lsquo;North&rsquo;

